<p data-start="176" data-end="198">The two main ones are:</p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="200" data-end="429" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="200" data-end="239"><tr data-start="200" data-end="239"><th data-start="200" data-end="210" data-col-size="sm" class="">Library</th><th data-start="210" data-end="217" data-col-size="sm" class="">Name</th><th data-start="217" data-end="239" data-col-size="sm" class="">Why traders use it</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="254" data-end="429"><tr data-start="254" data-end="337"><td data-start="254" data-end="268" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="256" data-end="267">XGBoost</strong></td><td data-start="268" data-end="296" data-col-size="sm">Extreme Gradient Boosting</td><td data-start="296" data-end="337" data-col-size="sm">very accurate, widely used in finance</td></tr><tr data-start="338" data-end="429"><td data-start="338" data-end="353" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="340" data-end="352">LightGBM</strong></td><td data-start="353" data-end="387" data-col-size="sm">Light Gradient Boosting Machine</td><td data-start="387" data-end="429" data-col-size="sm">faster than XGBoost for large datasets</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 32.7969px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<p data-start="431" data-end="471">You were likely thinking of <strong data-start="459" data-end="470">XGBoost</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="473" data-end="476">
